  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a study of the inflammatory reaction in standard 4 port laparoscopic cholecystectomy
      vs Single Port Laparoscopic (SIL) cholecystectomy. It is assumed that the reduced trauma in
      SIL Cholecystectomy causes reduced inflammatory reaction compared to the 4 port laparoscopic
      cholecystectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Two groups of 20 patients each are included in this study. Pre operatively, 6 and 24 hours
      postoperatively, blood is taken from these patients, it is centrifuged and the plasma is
      taken. IL-6, a-defensins and CRP are measured for each sample.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
